examples.en: The evidence argues for your claim.
He argues very strongly for his proposal.
That couple argues hourly, about everything.
Mills argues that high taxation strangles the economy.
The statement argues a change of attitude by the management.
She argues that racism is dangerous and corrosive to society.
Granovetter argues that institutions can be seen as "congealed networks".
The author argues that deterrence is no longer the best way to prevent war.
He argues that people in a community have certain obligations to each other.
He argues that placing too many requirements on schools devalues the education they provide.
He argues that a new toll is needed to pay for the long-term sustentation of the city's bridges.
He argues that there is an inextricable link between poverty and poor health.
